---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';
import ArtworkSchema from '../../../components/seo/ArtworkSchema.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'Nuevas Floras do Sul';

const img1 = (await import('../../../assets/images/obras/nuevas-floras-do-sul/do-sul-01.jpg')).default;
const img2 = (await import('../../../assets/images/obras/nuevas-floras-do-sul/do-sul-02.jpg')).default;
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="Nuevas Floras do Sul — Work"
  description="Nuevas Floras do Sul (2011). Sculptural intervention on trees. Jesuit ruins, southern Brazil. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>

  <ArtworkSchema
    title="Nuevas Floras do Sul"
    year="2011"
    medium="Sculptural intervention on trees"
    description="Version of Nuevas Floras made in southern Brazil, near the Jesuit ruins. Baroque carvings on trees dialogue with the historical Baroque of the Jesuit missions."
    url="https://mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/nuevas-floras-do-sul/"
  />

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 005c</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2011 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Sculptural intervention on trees &nbsp;/&nbsp; Jesuit ruins, southern Brazil</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <img src={img1.src} alt="Nuevas Floras do Sul — Sculptural intervention on a tree near the Jesuit ruins" loading="eager">
        <img src={img2.src} alt="Nuevas Floras do Sul — Detail of Baroque carving in dialogue with the mission ruins" loading="lazy">
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            <em>Nuevas Floras do Sul</em> is the version of <em>Nuevas Floras</em> realized
            in southern Brazil, in the vicinity of the Jesuit mission ruins. Escallon
            intervenes living trees with Baroque-form carvings — the same procedure originally
            developed in Colombia in 2003 — but here the geographic and historical context
            adds a particular dimension.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The Baroque carvings on the trees enter into direct dialogue with the historical
            Baroque of the ruined Jesuit missions. The Jesuit reductions of southern Brazil,
            founded in the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries, were centers of artistic
            production where European Baroque ornamentation merged with indigenous Guarani
            traditions. The ruins of those missions preserve fragments of that cultural
            hybridization.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            By carving Baroque forms onto living trees alongside those ruins, Escallon
            produces a temporal echo: the Baroque is once again inscribed upon nature, but
            this time in an artistic gesture conscious of the history that precedes it. The
            trees, as in all versions of <em>Nuevas Floras</em>, will over time respond by
            absorbing and transforming the intervention — making visible the relationship
            between culture and nature that the Jesuit missions also embodied in their
            own way.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">RELATED WORKS</h3>
          <ul style="margin-top: var(--s2); list-style: none;">
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              <a href="/maria-elvira-escallon/en/works/nuevas-floras/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">Nuevas Floras (2003) — Colombia</a>
            </li>
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              <a href="/maria-elvira-escallon/en/works/nuevas-floras-versalles/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">Nuevas Floras Versalles (2017) — France</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>Nuevas Floras do Sul</strong><br>
            2011<br><br>
            Sculptural intervention on trees.<br>
            Wood carving.<br><br>
            Variable dimensions.<br>
            Jesuit ruins, southern Brazil.
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">LOCATION</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Southern Brazil<br>
            Vicinity of the Jesuit mission ruins
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2011). <em>Nuevas Floras do Sul</em>.
            Sculptural intervention on trees. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/nuevas-floras-do-sul/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>
